# No Cursor git attribution

Never add any of the following to git commits, commit messages, or PR descriptions:

- `Co-authored-by: Cursor <cursoragent@cursor.com>`
- `Made-with: Cursor`
- Any other Cursor / cursoragent attribution trailer

When committing for this repo:

- Do not use `git commit --amend` if it would re-inject Cursor trailers.
- Prefer `git commit-tree` or a commit hook if Cursor keeps appending co-author lines.
- Never push commits that credit Cursor as author or co-author.

Only human contributors (e.g. repo owner and named collaborators) may appear in commit metadata.
